explanation:
No controlling expressions in this function are invariant. There are no loops (for/while/do) with constant conditions, and every conditional depends on runtime values or function results: 
- if (pos > SSIZE_MAX) depends on the pos parameter;
- if (NULL == src) depends on malloc returning NULL or not;
- if (0 == r_size) depends on the result of fread;
- the ternary using ferror(...) depends on stream state;
- if (MHD_YES != compress_buf(...)) depends on the return value of compress_buf.
All controlling expressions can vary at runtime, so none appear to violate MISRA C 2023 Rule 14.3 (the allowed exceptions for intentional infinite loops or the do-while constant-false case are not present).
